oai_dc:dc.dc:title: The Challenging Future of Food Animal Practice
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Robertson, Edwin G.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: food animal practice
veterinary medicine
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: What can offer more challenges and areas of growth for the future than Veterinary Medicine? What will we face as dairy practitioners if price supports are ended? What will we do in beef practice, feedlot practice, and especially embryo transfer practice if flat tax programs go into effect and the incentives for tax shelters are gone from the cattle industry?
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: American Association of Bovine Practitioners Conference Proceedings; 1984; 12-13
